Navigation behavior
Primary navigation uses six items in a fixed order: Home, Framework, Solutions, Insights, About, Contact. Secondary navigation appears within Framework, Solutions, Insights, and About. It must behave consistently across all four sections — same placement, same visual style, same selected state and hover/focus states, same routing pattern.

MOBILE NAVIGATION	Primary navigation on mobile uses a hamburger-style collapsed menu. It expands on tap and collapses on selection or outside tap.
Secondary navigation on mobile uses a horizontally scrollable tab row — consistently across all sections. It must not vary by section.

Detail page generation
Framework entries, Solution entries, Insight entries, and About Profile entries each require detail pages. These pages must be generated automatically from the corresponding CMS entry. They must not be manually created. The required content for each detail page is:

Framework detail	Title, category, summary and detail content, related solutions and insights if available, CTA path
Solution detail	Title, category, summary and detail content, related insights if available, CTA path
Insight detail	Title, category, publish date, author or source label, detail content, related content if available
About profile detail	Name, role/title, profile image, full bio content — required if the listing pattern uses summary cards

Contact page and inquiry flow
The Contact page is a single view. It must contain: contact intro, inquiry form, contact details, response expectation statement, and footer.

The inquiry form must include these fields:

Name	Label: "Your name"  —  required
Email	Label: "Work email"  —  required
Organization	Label: "Organization"  —  optional
Inquiry type	Label: "What can we help you with?"  —  required
Message	Label: "Tell us a bit about your need"  —  required Helper text: "A short description is enough for an initial response."

VALIDATION MESSAGES — Use the exact text defined in the Site Configuration Record Section 2.4. Do not invent validation error strings. Required field errors, format errors, and submission failure messages are all governed operational values.

After successful submission, display: "Thanks. Your inquiry has been received."
Response expectation statement: "We typically respond within two business days."

The inquiry submission creates an internal record with workflow status Submitted. Admin users can move it to Under Review, Responded, or Closed. Contributors cannot change workflow status.

FORM REQUIREMENTS	Every input must have a persistent visible label — placeholder text must not be used as the sole label.
Validation errors must be field-specific and visually aligned with the relevant input.
Success and error states must be clearly communicated — both visually and programmatically.
All forms must include spam / abuse mitigation appropriate to the platform.
Client-side validation must be mirrored server-side.

