SECTION 6
SEO, Accessibility, and Performance

SEO and metadata
Every public page must have a unique, descriptive page title. Page title patterns from the Site Configuration Record:

Site Page	{page_title} | Plenor.ai
Solution entry	{entry_title} | Solutions | Plenor.ai
Framework entry	{entry_title} | Framework | Plenor.ai
Insight entry	{entry_title} | Insights | Plenor.ai
About profile entry	{entry_title} | About | Plenor.ai

These patterns apply only when a CMS entry does not define its own title or description. Boilerplate metadata repeated across multiple pages is not permitted.

URLs must be descriptive, stable, and human-readable with hyphen-separated words. When a slug changes, implement a redirect. Do not leave broken internal links.

Structured data mappings: Home = WebSite, Framework / Solutions / About / Contact pages = WebPage, Insight entries = Article, Organisation identity = Organization.

Sitemap: include all published canonical public pages. Exclude draft, in-review, preview, and admin URLs. Crawl frequency: Home and Insights weekly, all others monthly.

Accessibility — WCAG 2.2 Level AA
The site must conform to WCAG 2.2 Level AA. The following must be confirmed at acceptance:

Page titles	Every public page has a unique, descriptive title
Headings	Descriptive and reflect page organisation — not decorative
Link text	Communicates destination or action clearly — not "click here" or "read more"
Images	All non-text content has appropriate alt text
Keyboard navigation	All navigation, forms, and interactive controls are keyboard-operable
Focus visibility	Focus indicator is visible for all interactive elements — focus ring color: #0F766E
Color contrast	All text meets WCAG 2.2 AA contrast ratios — state communication does not rely on color alone
Form errors	Errors are field-specific, visually aligned, and programmatically announced

Performance
Performance is a monitored quality obligation for the current phase — not a numeric gate unless thresholds are separately declared. The following must be completed before acceptance:

Core Web Vitals	Monitor for all public pages where data is available
Template review	No major page template accepted without performance review on mobile and desktop
Media and scripts	Large images, scripts, and third-party embeds must not unnecessarily degrade page experience

